data.abstract: How to Check for Violations. Motorists can verify potential violations by entering their plate number or conduction number along with their MV File Number on mayhulika.mmda.gov.ph. You can find your MV File Number on your vehicle’s OR/CR. If a violation is found, a Notice of Violation (NOV) will be sent via postal mail within five to seven days.
